The board of education of each school district may contribute the levy equivalent tax rate of five cents ($0.05) and equalization funds for energy conservation measures under guaranteed energy savings contracts pursuant to KRS 45A.345, 45A.352, and 45A.353. Use of these funds, as provided under KRS 45A.353, 56.774, and 58.600 shall be based on the following guidelines:
Energy conservation measures shall include facility alteration;
Energy conservation measures shall be identified in the district's approved facility plan pursuant to KRS 157.420;
The current facility systems are consuming excess maintenance and operating costs;
The savings generated by the energy conservation measures are guaranteed;
The levy equivalent tax rate of five cents ($0.05) and equalization funds contributed to the energy conservation measures shall be defined as capital cost avoidance as provided in KRS 45A.345(2) and shall be subject to the restrictions on usage as specified in KRS 45A.352(9); and
The equipment that is replaced has exceeded its useful life as determined by a life cycle cost analysis.
